			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Disease quest</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=39125"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:lord_paradigm@hotmail.com">Sylas (E'Ci Server)</a> | 
		                        11/12/1999 2:24:51 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">ok this quest starts off really simple...your in the shrine of bertoxxulous in the qeynos catacombs.  talk to the guy in the far far back of the shrine i forgot his name, anyway, he tells you to see commander Kane Bayle.  If you wait until dark, Commander Kane comes to the shrine.  Hail him and tell him the disease is spreading.(whatever you do, dont say the name Antonius Bayle around kane, he gets angry).  Kane gives you a no drop bottle of Blackburrow Stout.  you have to take this to Born Bloodstone in Highpass, he stands next to the golden rooster. born gives you a note #1 of 3 and tells you to go to Freeport and to talk to a lady Named Opal Darkbriar.<BR>
<BR>
Here's the aggravating part.  There are 4 different NPCs named Opal Darkbriar....i cant find the correct one...you are suppose to tell her that the disease is spreading, she will give you letter #2 and your next destination.<BR>
i have spent 2 RL days doing this quest over and over and searching freeport for this stupid NPC.  i know its not the one in the academy of arcane sciences and i know its not the one in the necromancers guild.  supposively a Opal Darkbriar spawns on the rocks to the right of the docks, but i have spent 12hours there and never found her.  can someone please help me out here? thanks.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
